            "content": "Headed by the Social Life Secretary and assistant. Responsible for all social events that bring parishioners together.\r\n\r\n<strong>Committee Composition:</strong>\r\n\r\n- Social Life Secretary and assistant\r\n- Mr. and Mrs. KUCC\r\n- Publicity secretaries of SCCs and other parish groups\r\n- Other passionate permanent members\r\n\r\n<strong>Objectives:</strong>\r\n\r\n- Enhance team building among parishioners\r\n- Foster unity among members from different backgrounds\r\n- Carry out social events successfully\r\n- Nurture talents among parishioners\r\n\r\n<strong>Annual Events:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>1. Fresher's Night</strong>\r\n\r\nUshers in first year students; gives them a chance to interact with parish members and leaders, delegates SCCs to them, and allows them to showcase talents.\r\n\r\n<strong>2. October Madness</strong>\r\n\r\nMid-semester event. Parishioners interact through games, dancing, modelling, and other activities. Enhances teambuilding and nurtures talents.\r\n\r\n<strong>3. Carol's Night</strong>\r\n\r\nPrepares parishioners for the Christmas season. Christmas songs, gifts, decorations. Various groups and SCCs present.\r\n\r\n<strong>4. Parish Census</strong>\r\n\r\nCarried out every academic year. Data collected: name, phone number, Jumuiya, church group, residence, home diocese, home parish, sacraments received.\r\n\r\n<strong>5. Talent Show</strong>\r\n\r\nGroups and individuals showcase talents — modelling, dancing, spoken word, singing, narratives. Culminates in crowning Mr. and Mrs. KUCC.\r\n\r\n<strong>6. Elder's Bash</strong>\r\n\r\nFarewell event for final-year students (parish elders). They present and give words of advice to those remaining."
